In this article, it is mentioned that the President of the United States, Barack Obama, had a phone call with the President of Turkey, Recep Tayyip Erdogan, to discuss Turkey's recent downing of a Russian aircraft. The President expressed support for Turkey's right to defend its sovereignty and NATO's support as well. The leaders emphasized the importance of deescalating the situation and working towards preventing similar incidents in the future. They also reaffirmed their commitment to fighting against ISIL.